Answer.feedback1: It was a problem quickly clicking the center and then going around (an invisible color wheel at first) to find the same color or face. It was like a weird guessing game since the positions of the colors and faces were always changing around the circle.
Answer.feedback2: The positioning of the colors or faces around the wheel was always changing....for example, sometimes the green was on the bottom, sometimes it was on the top, or sometimes the female faces were on the right of the wheel and sometimes they were on the left. It was annoying to guess where they were because the colors or faces on the wheel didn't appear until after I clicked the outer wheel!  It was more like a guessing game....for example... will the blue color be on the right or left...I don't know....I have to go around the wheel and guess and then it appears after I click!  It would have been better if they were always in the same spot around the wheel, especially since I couldn't see it until I clicked it.
Answer.feedback3: Finding the "second" image (and ignoring the first) was too difficult with the time limit...It wasn't clear when each task was starting....for example...I saw the first color or face, but the second one didn't seem to appear unless I clicked and then it got confusing and there wasn't enough time to go around the circle and match it on a circle which was invisible until I clicked it. My suggestion is not to have to click the center of the circle for anything. Just have the center change as the mouse is moved around the circle to match what is at the sides and let the circle be visible before I have to click it and let the colors or faces be consistently in the same spot, since it takes time to find them on the invisible wheel (which appears after I have clicked it) .  (I scored less at this section because of the confusion with the more complicated technicalities.) Please test run the tasks yourself and test-trial them first before you give them to us.  Thanks.
